nue in the next year.\n*   **Growth Drivers (from MD&A):** Recent revenue growth has been driven by the **Connectivity segment** (Starlink subscriber growth) and, for 2025, increased **Launch & Development** revenue from government contracts (NASA, U.S. Department of War).\n\n### **Key Notes:**\n*   **Segment Breakdown:** The provided excerpts do not break down backlog by business segment (Space, Connectivity, AI).\n*   **Contract Duration:** For context, the revenue recognition policies note that:\n    *   **Connectivity mobile agreements** are generally multi-year (1-5 years) but terminable by the customer.\n    *   **Starshield contracts** are long-term, using the cost-to-cost method.\n    *   **Launch Services** contracts range from one to five years; **Launch & Development** contracts can extend up to fourteen years.',
